---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for Property Management Australia.">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-pma-navy text-white py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="w-16 h-1 bg-pma-sky mx-auto mb-4"></div>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">Effective Date: 27 June 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Property Management Australia (Qld) Pty Ltd (ACN 664 489 632), trading as Property Management Australia ("we", "us", "our"), is committed to protecting the privacy of your personal information. We are a subsidiary of FRM Consulting Group (Aust) Pty Ltd (ACN 630 110 682).
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, hold, use, disclose and otherwise manage personal information in accordance with the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth) ("Privacy Act") and the Australian Privacy Principles ("APPs").
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        By using our website, engaging our services or otherwise providing us with your personal information, you consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <!-- APPs Reference -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">2. Australian Privacy Principles</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We are bound by the APPs contained in the Privacy Act. The APPs regulate how organisations may collect, use, disclose and store personal information, and how individuals may access and correct personal information held about them. More information about the APPs is available from the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner ("OAIC") at
        <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-pma-sky hover:underline">www.oaic.gov.au</a>.
      </p>

      <!-- What is Personal Information -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">3. What is Personal Information?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Personal information is information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable, whether the information or opinion is true or not, and whether the information or opinion is recorded in a material form or not. Common examples include your name, address, email address, phone number and date of birth.
      </p>

      <!-- Collection Methods -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">4. How We Collect Personal Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We collect personal information in a variety of ways, including:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Directly from you, when you provide information by phone, email, online forms, in person or through our website</li>
        <li>From third parties such as referral partners, property developers, financial institutions, real estate agents, and other service providers</li>
        <li>From publicly available sources, including public registers, social media platforms and online directories</li>
        <li>Through our website via cookies, analytics tools and other tracking technologies</li>
        <li>When you attend our events, seminars or webinars</li>
        <li>When you apply for a position with us</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Where it is reasonable and practicable to do so, we will collect your personal information directly from you. If we receive personal information about you from a third party, we will take reasonable steps to ensure you are made aware of the matters set out in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <!-- Purposes -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">5. Why We Collect, Hold, Use and Disclose Personal Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We collect, hold, use and disclose your personal information for the following purposes:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>To provide you with our products, services and information</li>
        <li>To manage and administer property investments, including those held within Self-Managed Super Funds (SMSFs)</li>
        <li>To communicate with you about our services, promotions, events and other offerings</li>
        <li>To process and respond to your enquiries, feedback and complaints</li>
        <li>To verify your identity and conduct due diligence checks</li>
        <li>To comply with our legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        <li>To improve our products, services, website and customer experience</li>
        <li>To manage our relationship with you</li>
        <li>To conduct market research and business analysis</li>
        <li>To recruit and manage staff, contractors and volunteers</li>
        <li>For any other purpose for which you have given your consent</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Sensitive Information -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">6. Sensitive Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Sensitive information is a subset of personal information that is afforded a higher level of protection under the Privacy Act. It includes information about your racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs, membership of professional or trade associations, sexual orientation, criminal record, health information, and biometric data.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We will only collect sensitive information where it is reasonably necessary for our functions or activities and you have consented to the collection, or the collection is required or authorised by law. All sensitive information will be treated with the highest level of care and security.
      </p>

      <!-- Direct Marketing -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">7. Direct Marketing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may use your personal information to send you marketing communications about our products, services, events and promotions that we believe may be of interest to you. These communications may be sent via email, SMS, telephone, direct mail or social media.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You can opt out of receiving marketing communications from us at any time by contacting us using the details set out at the end of this Privacy Policy, or by using the unsubscribe facility in our electronic communications. We will process your opt-out request as soon as reasonably practicable.
      </p>

      <!-- Cookies and Tracking -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">8. Cookies and Website Tracking</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Our website may use cookies, web beacons, pixels and other tracking technologies to collect information about your browsing behaviour, device and preferences. This information helps us improve our website, personalise your experience and analyse website traffic.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Cookies are small data files stored on your device when you visit a website. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings. Please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of our website.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may also use third-party analytics services, such as Google Analytics, to help us understand how visitors use our website. These services may collect information about your visits to our website, including the pages you view, the links you click, and other actions you take on our site. This information is used in aggregate form to improve our website and services.
      </p>

      <!-- Disclosure -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">9. Disclosure of Personal Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may disclose your personal information to third parties in the following circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>To our parent company, FRM Consulting Group (Aust) Pty Ltd (ACN 630 110 682), and its other subsidiaries, for internal administrative purposes, shared services, and to provide you with integrated products and services across the group</li>
        <li>To our employees, contractors, agents and service providers who assist us in operating our business, including IT service providers, marketing agencies, accountants, auditors and legal advisors</li>
        <li>To financial institutions, property developers, real estate agents, property managers and other parties involved in property transactions</li>
        <li>To government agencies, regulators and law enforcement bodies as required or authorised by law</li>
        <li>To professional advisors, including lawyers, accountants and insurers</li>
        <li>To any other third party where you have provided your consent</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We take reasonable steps to ensure that any third parties to whom we disclose your personal information are bound by obligations of confidentiality and privacy that are at least as restrictive as those set out in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <!-- Overseas Disclosure -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">10. Overseas Disclosure</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may disclose personal information to overseas recipients where it is necessary to provide our services or where you have consented to such disclosure. Where we do disclose personal information overseas, we will take reasonable steps to ensure that the overseas recipient handles your personal information in accordance with the APPs.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Some of the third-party service providers we use, such as cloud storage, email and analytics providers, may store data on servers located outside of Australia. We take reasonable steps to ensure these providers are bound by laws or contractual obligations that provide a comparable level of protection of your personal information.
      </p>

      <!-- Security -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">11. Security of Personal Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from misuse, interference, loss, unauthorised access, modification and disclosure. These measures include:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Using secure servers and encrypted communications</li>
        <li>Restricting access to personal information to authorised personnel only</li>
        <li>Implementing password protection and multi-factor authentication</li>
        <li>Regularly reviewing and updating our security practices and systems</li>
        <li>Training our staff on privacy and data security obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        When we no longer require your personal information for the purposes for which it was collected, and we are not required by law to retain it, we will take reasonable steps to destroy or de-identify it.
      </p>

      <!-- Access and Correction -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">12. Access to and Correction of Personal Information</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you. You also have the right to request that we correct any personal information that is inaccurate, out-of-date, incomplete, irrelevant or misleading.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        To make a request for access or correction, please contact us using the details set out at the end of this Privacy Policy. We will respond to your request within a reasonable period of time and, where reasonable, give access to or correct the information in the manner you have requested.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may charge a reasonable fee for providing access to your personal information to cover our administrative costs. We will not charge you for making a request for access or correction, or for making any corrections to your personal information.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        In some circumstances, we may refuse to provide access to or correct your personal information. If we do, we will provide you with written reasons for the refusal and the mechanisms available to you to complain about the refusal.
      </p>

      <!-- Complaints -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">13. Complaints</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you believe that we have breached the APPs or otherwise mishandled your personal information, you may lodge a complaint with us using the contact details set out below. We will acknowledge your complaint within a reasonable time and investigate it promptly. We will notify you of the outcome of our investigation within 30 days.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you are not satisfied with our response, you may lodge a complaint with the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC):
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li>Online: <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/privacy-complaints" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-pma-sky hover:underline">www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/privacy-complaints</a></li>
        <li>Phone: 1300 363 992</li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:enquiries@oaic.gov.au" class="text-pma-sky hover:underline">enquiries@oaic.gov.au</a></li>
        <li>Mail: GPO Box 5218, Sydney NSW 2001</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Updates -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">14. Updates to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements or other factors. Any changes will be posted on our website with an updated effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your personal information.
      </p>

      <!-- Contact Details -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-pma-navy mb-4 mt-10">15. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, wish to make a complaint, or would like to request access to or correction of your personal information, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Entity:</strong> Property Management Australia (Qld) Pty Ltd (ACN 664 489 632)</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:admin@frmcg.com.au" class="text-pma-sky hover:underline">admin@frmcg.com.au</a></li>
        <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:0417548823" class="text-pma-sky hover:underline">0417 548 823</a></li>
        <li><strong>Address:</strong> Suite 22 Level 1, 21 South Coolum Rd, Coolum Beach QLD 4573</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
